    Actions in Combat

  Standard Actions
# Strike (1): Make one melee or ranged attack with your weapon's stats. Roll a d20 + MGT or FIN vs target's AC. Apply damage on success.
# Move (1): Move up to your characterâ€™s speed. This can be broken up before and after actions unless otherwise stated.
# Cast (1-3): Use one of your abilities or a spell. 
# Interact (1): Draw or stow a weapon, interact with the enviroment or throw an item.
# Defend (1): You brace yourself for a hit. Raise your AC by +1 until your next turn.
# Ready (1-3): Prepare an action to trigger later in response to a specific condition being met at any point in this round of combat.
# Use Item (1): Use an item in your inventory, drink a potion, use a scroll.
# Search (1): Actively look for traps, secret doors, or weaknesses. Roll a WIL saving throw with DC appropriate for the situation. You discover something about the enviroment or the enemy.

  Battle Actions
# Manevuer (1-3): Perform a special melee or ranged weapon attack unique to a weapon.
# Disengage (2): Move half your speed without provoking attacks of opportunity.
# Dash (2): Move double your regular speed this turn, disables the move action on this turn.
# Grapple (2): Attempt to grapple an adjacent opponent. Roll a MGT check against their MGT, on a success the target gains the restrained condition.
# Aim (1): Take aim with your ranged weapon. Gain a +3 to your next attack roll with a ranged weapon.
# Feint (1): Attempt to trick an opponent lowering their AC. Roll a FIN check against their WIL, on a success the target's AC is lowered by -2.
# Taunt (1): Attempt to focus the attention of the enemy on yourself. Roll a PRS check against their WIL, on a success the target will focus their attention on you for 1 round.
# Disarm (2): Attempt to make an enemy drop their weapon. Roll a FIN check against their FIN, on a success the target drops one of their weapons to the ground.
# Push (1): Attempt to push an enemy away or drop them on the ground. Roll a MGT check against their MGT, on a success the target is pushed away 5ft.
